Title : List of Death in Paradise episodes
Text : {{Use British English|date=October 2016}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}
''[[Death in Paradise (TV series)|Death in Paradise]]'' is a British and French [[Police procedural|crime drama]] created by [[Robert Thorogood]].<ref name="Thorogood">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/mediapacks/deathinparadise/thorogood|title=New BBC One drama starring Ben Miller and Sara Martins: Robert Thorogood|last=Thorogood|first=Robert|date=17 October 2011|work=[[BBC Media Centre]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|accessdate=2 February 2018}}</ref> The show is set in the fictional Caribbean island of [[Saint Marie (fictional island)|Saint Marie]], and is filmed in [[Guadeloupe]].<ref name="Saint Marie">{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/travel/destinations/caribbean/articles/Death-in-Paradise-Guadeloupe-the-real-life-St-Marie/|title=Death in Paradise: Guadeloupe, the real-life Saint Marie|date=5 January 2016|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]]|accessdate=2 February 2018}}</ref> The series focuses on a [[detective inspector]] (DI) and his police team solving murder mysteries on the Caribbean island. The programme's main cast has included [[Ben Miller]], who starred as DI [[Richard Poole (character)|Richard Poole]] from 2011 to 2014, [[Kris Marshall]], who portrayed DI [[Humphrey Goodman]] from 2014 to 2017, [[Ardal O'Hanlon]], who currently plays DI Jack Mooney, [[Gary Carr (actor)|Gary Carr]] who portrayed [[sergeant]] Fidel Best from 2011 to 2014, [[Sara Martins]], who starred as detective sergeant (DS) [[Camille Bordey]] from 2011 to 2015, [[Joséphine Jobert]] from 2015 to 2019 in the role of DS Florence Cassell (until Season 8, Episode 6)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/news/josephine-jobert-why-quit-florence-death-in-paradise-568810/|title=Death in Paradise star Josephine Jobert: Why I took the ‘tough decision’ to quit as Florence
|last=Hollingsworth|first=David|date=19 February 2019|accessdate=19 February 2019}}</ref>, [[Don Warrington]] who has starred as [[commissioner]] Selwyn Patterson since the first episode, [[Danny John-Jules]], who played [[police officer|officer]] Dwayne Myers from 2011 to 2018,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/news/strictlys-danny-john-jules-left-death-paradise-551857/|title=Danny John-Jules: Why I left Death in Paradise as Officer Dwayne Myers|last=Bullimore|first=Emma|date=2 October 2018|work=[[What's on TV]]|publisher=[[TI Media]]|accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref> Tobi Bakare who currently portrays officer JP Hooper and [[Élizabeth Bourgine]], who has played the character Catherine Bordey since series one.<ref name="BBC Characters">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/5NBydTwDZryNHPG17f3lLBp/characters|title=Characters|work=[[BBC Online]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|accessdate=3 February 2018}}</ref>

''Death in Paradise'' was first announced on 9 December 2010 by the [[BBC]]; commissioned by controller of BBC Drama Commissioning [[Ben Stephenson]]. It was revealed that the show would be produced by Red Planet Pictures and Atlantique Productions, in association with [[BBC Worldwide]] and [[Kudos (production company)|Kudos Film and Television]] for [[BBC One]] and [[France Télévisions]].<ref name="BBC announce">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/pressoffice/pressreleases/stories/2010/12_december/09/paradise.shtml|title=Ambitious new drama series Death In Paradise for BBC One and France Televisions|date=9 December 2010|work=BBC Press Office|publisher=[[BBC]]|accessdate=3 February 2018}}</ref> The idea for ''Death in Paradise'' came from Robert Thorogood, whose idea was formed after reading a report of a suspected murder in the Caribbean during the Cricket World Cup.<ref name="Thorogood"/> Filming for the first series began in spring 2011,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/news/a292308/bbc-announces-drama-death-in-paradise/|title=BBC announce drama 'Death In Paradise'|last=Wightman|first=Catriona|date=9 December 2010|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]]|accessdate=3 February 2018}}</ref> with the first series airing between October and December 2011.<ref name=Series1AirDate/> On 11 January 2012, Stephenson announced that a second series comprising eight episodes had been commissioned.<ref name=Series2Renewal/> The second series ran from January to February 2013. Since then, ''Death in Paradise'' has been recommissioned each year,<ref name=Series3Renewal/><ref name=Series4Renewal/><ref name=Series4Renewal_b/><ref name=Series6Renewal/><ref name=Series7Renewal/> and aired in January of each following year.<ref name=Series4AirDate/><ref name=Series5AirDate/><ref name=Series7AirDate/><ref name=Series8Renewal/>

A ninth and tenth series were announced at the conclusion of series eight on 28 February 2019<ref name=Series9+10Renewal/>

